\par\par \b \uc2  Leadership change 'not the answer to  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  woes'. \b0\par\par\uc2 732 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Rizal Ramli asserted on Wednesday that a change in national leadership was not the answer to the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems because such a change would not secure "minimum political stability." \par \par \uc2  "What we need is not that (a change in national leadership), but minimum political stability," Rizal told a seminar on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  held by the National Defense Institution (Lemhanas). \par \par \uc2  "If there is minimum political stability and legal certainty, whoever the leader may be, I'm sure Indonesia can come out of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis quickly and become one of the great nations in the region," he added. \par \par \uc2  Rizal warned, however, that achieving political stability via the old military approach as occurred during the 32-year rule of former authoritarian president Soeharto would be detrimental and costly to the country. \par \par \uc2  Several top economists have earlier insisted that resolving the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problem is only possible if the embattled President Abdurrahman Wahid steps down, and hands over power to popular Vice President Megawati Sukarnoputri. \par \par \uc2  The pressure for Abdurrahman to step down has intensified after the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  issued a second censure against the President on April 30 over alleged involvement in two financial scandals and his incompetence in governing effectively. \par \par \uc2  Reports said that Abdurrahman, Megawati and a team of seven senior ministers, including Rizal, have been engaged in serious talks to seek a "compromise" to resolve the national leadership crisis. \par \par \uc2  The political crisis has contributed to the drop in the value of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar and rising domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which in turn threatens the 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  by reaching a critical level of up to 6 percent of gross domestic product (GDP), compared to the initial projection of 3.7 percent of GDP. \par \par \uc2  The government may also have to cut down its earlier \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth forecast for this year to 3.5 percent from 5 percent. The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  contracted by 14 percent in 1998, registered a relatively flat growth in 1999, and grew by 4.8 percent last year. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Abdurrahman has been quoted as saying that if he stepped down, the country's political condition might worsen with the strong likelihood of national disintegration. \par \par \uc2  "The problem is politics ... If we can't resolve the crisis of confidence (in the current government), the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problem can not be resolved," said top political economist Didik Rachbini, who is also one of the speakers in the seminar. \par \par \uc2  Didik said that one way to restore confidence in the government was for Abdurrahman to rebuild a coalition government, although he admitted that it would now be a very difficult task after the President himself dissolved his previous coalition Cabinet. \par \par \uc2  He said that forming a coalition government was crucial for the survival of a President under current political conditions where his party commanded only 11 percent of the 500-seat \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  But Rizal insisted that it would be useless for the President to appoint ministers from opposing political parties if the parties did not support particular ministers as happened during the early months of the administration of Abdurrahman in late 1999. \par \par \uc2  "I agree with the suggestion to form a coalition, but the appointed ministers must deliver and their parties must support their policies," he said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Miranda Goeltom, who also addressed the seminar, said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had to be consistent with its monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to help maintain confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as developments in other fronts, particularly politics, had been discouraging. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  had to maintain its tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , by allowing the interest rate to continue to increase due to high inflationary pressures from imports and the weakening rupiah amid domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Of course, there will be costs that we have to bear (larger interest costs to the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ), but we should try to minimize the cost," she said. \par \par \uc2  The benchmark interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  SBI notes increased again on Wednesday to 16.26 percent from 16.06 percent previously. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have said that the continuing increase in the SBI rate is threatening the country's weak banking sector and causing heavier burdens to the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which covers the interest charges of massive government bonds issued to finance the recapitalization of domestic banks. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpo