rs, he said. \par \par \uc2  "We estimate retailer expansion in opening new outlets this year to grow by 7 percent." \par \par \uc2  The estimated growth in expansion this year is similar to the 8 percent expansion growth prior to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in 1997. \par \par \uc2  Expansion declined to less than 1 percent between 1998 and 1999 as retailers halted their expansion programs to cope with the impact of the country's worst ever \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis which peaked in 1998. \par \par \uc2  Last year expansion rebounded to 4 percent due to the improvement in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  According to Kustarjono, both large and small companies had expanded aggressively. \par \par \uc2  Sogo will open an outlet in Surabaya, and Matahari will also open new outlets in several cities this year, he added. "Thousands of mini supermarkets will also open this year," he added.(05) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5c000lx\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
