\par\par \b \uc2  Over $25b in foreign debt matures in 2001. \b0\par\par\uc2 640 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) deputy governor Burhanudin Abdullah said that the country's overseas debt maturing this year reached some US$25.39 billion. \par \par \uc2  Burhanudin told a weekend gathering with reporters at Anyer, West Java, that the total consisted of $4.3 billion in sovereign debt and $21.01 billion in private sector debt. \par \par \uc2  He was quoted by Satunet online as saying that the private sector debt comprised of $11.54 billion owed by domestic companies, $1.9 billion by the banking sector and $7.5 billion by foreign companies operating in the country. \par \par \uc2  Burhanudin said that the country's outstanding overseas debt, as of January, totaled $140.2 billion consisting of $74.2 billion in sovereign debt and $66 billion in private sector debt. \par \par \uc2  The relatively huge amount of foreign debt, particularly corporate debt maturing this year, would add additional pressure on the ailing rupiah unless the debts are restructured. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah recently dropped to a 31-month low of more than Rp 12,000 per U.S. dollar due to a combination of domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  woes. The rupiah managed to strengthen to around Rp 11,300 per dollar last week. \par \par \uc2  But with slow progress in the restructuring of the corporate foreign debt, the rupiah would continue to be under pressure, analysts said. \par \par \uc2  But experts have warned that the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector debts were also a critical problem that could cause major new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  woes unless measures are taken to reduce them to a manageable level. \par \par \uc2  Besides being burdened with $74.2 billion in foreign debt, the government is also reeling under Rp 600 trillion ($60 billion) in domestic debt, thereby making the total amount of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector debt greater than the country's gross domestic product (Rp 1,290.6 trillion at current market prices). \par \par \uc2  The huge domestic debt is the resulting cost of financing the country's largest ever bank restructuring and recapitalization program. \par \par \uc2  The government is planning to reduce its domestic debt by pushing the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA), a unit under the finance ministry, to speed up the sales of assets. \par \par \uc2  Analysts, however, said that IBRA's performance had so far been disappointing partly due to strong resistance from certain powerful businessmen who did not want to see their previously-owned assets fall into the hands of new foreign owners. \par \par \uc2  IBRA has taken over more than Rp 600 trillion worth of assets from ailing banks and former bank owners who owed huge debts to the government. \par \par \uc2  The government must also continue to seek restructuring facilities from its international creditors, particularly sovereign creditors grouped in the Paris Club to avoid defaulting. \par \par \uc2  The government is scheduled to meet the Paris Club later this month to discuss the restructuring of Indonesia's sovereign debt. \par \par \uc2  But the support of the Paris Club would only be obtained if the government managed to gain the International Monetary Fund's (IMF) seal of approval for its new reform package. \par \par \uc2  In fact, the restructuring facility promised by the Paris Club last year for some $2.8 billion in sovereign debt could be canceled if the government failed to sign a new agreement with the IMF soon. \par \par \uc2  The IMF, which canceled its loan disbursement to the country late last year, has said that it would only agree to resume discussions on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  program with the government after the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  approved the revision of the 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The government is currently finalizing the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revision, and plans to submit it to the House sometime this week. \par \par \uc2  The state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  has to be revised as various assumptions it adopted in January are no longer valid due to the sharp drop in the value of the rupiah and the rising domestic interest rate. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5e000ks\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Rupiah end lower on political conflicts prior parliamentary session. \b0\par\par\uc2 397 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 May 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended lower against the US$ by 125 \par \par \uc2  (1.11%) to \par \par \uc2  11,400 due to unclear solution to political problems prior the \par \par \uc2  parliamentary \par \par \uc2  session at the end of this month. \par \par \uc2  Managing Director of Bank Buana Indonesia Pardi Kendy predicted the \par \par \uc2  political condition would heat up prior the parliamentary meeting at the \par \par \uc2  end \par \par \uc2  of this month. \par \par \uc2  "Especially since the political elites are still in dispute and held on to \par \par \uc2  their opinions. The market sees no clear direction to political solutions \par \par \uc2  until now," he said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Pardi added the market would react if the political elites reach a \par \par \uc2  compromise because political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  could lead to fear of mass \par \par \uc2  riots. \par \par \uc2  "Its true that nothing has not happened so far. But the market would react \par \par \uc2  positively if the political elites reach a compromise that could solve the \par \par \uc2  conflicts," he said. \par \par \uc2  The Telerate data showed that the rupiah ended at 11,400 per US$ at the \par \par \uc2  Jakarta spot market yesterday, weaker compared to Friday's position \par \par \uc2  of11,275. The rupiah ranged between 11,200 and 11,445. The rupiah was \par \par \uc2  traded \par \par \uc2  at the international market (at19.00) at around 11,425. \par \par \uc2  According to Pardi, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors did not have much impact on the \par \par \uc2  rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "The market seemed to have forgotten about the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factor. Even the \par \par \uc2  large inflation revision did not have much affect, as well as the Fed's \par \par \uc2  decision to lower rates, which should have brought positive impacts." \par \par \uc2  Further weakening in the rupiah could lead to higher \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . BI \par \par \uc2  officials have warned the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  could reach 17%. "So the chance \par \par \uc2  that the rates would continue to go up is possible," he said. \par \par \uc2  BI enters market \par \par \uc2  A dealer of a private bank said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  was seen intervening in \par \par \uc2  the \par \par \uc2  market by selling US$ through a number of state banks. \par \par \uc2  "When the rupiah reached 11,300 and continued to weaken, some state banks \par \par \uc2  were seen selling US$. This is of course part of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's efforts \par \par \uc2  to curb rupiah depreciation," he said. \par \par \uc2  Furthermore he predicted the rupiah depreciation would continue to take \par \par \uc2  place this week. "It won't be long until it reaches the 11,500-11,700 \par \par \uc2  level. \par \par \uc2  But the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  will continue to hold back the rupiah from sliding \par \par \uc2  further to the psychological level of 12,000 per US$," said the dealer. \par \par \uc2  (yn). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010710dx5f000pe\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
