\par\par \b \uc2  TUESDAY 15th May 2001, EDITORIALS IN INDONESIA'S MAJOR DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 885 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 May 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited.< Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its\par \par \uc2  THIRTEEN DAYS TO GO Perhaps it would be necessary to remind President Wahid that his show of obstinacy and hardheadedness are causing great inconvenience and added suffering to the lower segment of the people whose quality of life has steadily worsened by the deteriorating \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition. Wahid and the NU leadership seem to overlook the principal fact that the censure motion against him has not been motivated in the first place because he has proved for more than a year that he lacks the leadership to lead a cabinet which delivers good performance, but primarily because he has been suspected of power abuse by removing Bulog funds amounting to Rp35 billion belonging to Bulog personnel and by putting in his pocket a US$2 million gift from Sultan Bolkiah of Brunei. \par \par \uc2   It may be that his refusal to answer the second memorandum is caused by his inability to produce a credible explanation of his innocence in these cases, but it is an established fact that Parliament will still insist that he should enlighten the people and give a full account in relation to the whole matter. - The Indonesian Observer \par \par \uc2  BROADENING THE \b \highlight22\uc2 TAX\b0 \highlight\uc2  BASE Easing the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden is, theoritically, one of the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  instruments usually employed by a government to reinvigorate a slumping \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The rationale is that a lighter \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden will increase the amount of disposable income of taxpayers, thereby bolstering their purchasing power and consequently strengthening private consumption so as to encourage \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity. This popular line of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reasoning should be quite relevant to Indonesia as its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is projected to be 1.5 to two percentage points lower than the original estimate of four percent to five percent made at the outset of the 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year in January. Such a populist program would also be quite attractive as a political instrument for a government like that of Abdurrahman Wahid whose popularity and credibility is declining sharply. The government is nonetheless being compelled to pursue the unpopular measure of stepping up its \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection campaign, which in many other countries would be the surest path to political suicide. In fact, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and excise duties are one of the five main \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  instrument being employed by the government to raise additional revenue so as to cover its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which for the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year is estimated to be about Rp30 trillion (US$2.7 billion) larger than the original projection of Rp53 trillion. There are, however, several factors and conditions in Indonesia that still allow for a more concerted \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  effort without causing more suffering for the people at large, who have been groaning under the strain of severe \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  hardship since the crisis broke out in late 1997. - The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2  THE TRUE SPIRIT OF THE INDONESIAN MILITARY Are we supposed to merely watch the intentions of some people to declare an Aceh Republic, Maluku Republic, Riau Republic, Papua Republic and - as we heard from President Wahid - a Madura Republic? The Indonesian military basically has two traditions: first, the tradition to follow political intentions, and second, the tradition - together with the people - to fight any intention to undermine the unity of Indonesia. In the last two years, thanks to reform and enrichment, the military has returned to its original role as a defense force, guardian of Indonesia's sovereignty. Guarding the country's sovereignty is a sacred mission which should be exercised without compromise. The military, however, seems to have gone too far back from the lines. It has been watching chaos in its surroundings that it has not taken separatism as a serious problem. Now, it is time for the military to implement strict measured in fulfilling its sacred duty of guarding the country's sovereignty. This however does not mean that the military should attempt to stage a coup. Under any circumstance, it is unacceptable for soldiers to engage in politics. Our bad experience during the 32-year New Order regime is a good reminder for the military not to go back to the political stage. - Media Indonesia \par \par \uc2  INDON DEBTS VERY CRITICAL We seem to have plunged into a bottomless pit. Indonesia has been under huge debts. The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's (BI) director, Burhanuddin Abdullah said, "Even all the people's income for one year would not be enough to repay the (country's) debts". How can we repay these debts, at least those which are due, amounting to US$ 4.2 billion? For the purpose, we have applied for and are offered new debts. This is a vicious cycle we are facing for an \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  period of time as the government's debts have reached US$ 74.22 billion. Coupled with the private sector's debts, the country's debts total US$ 140.21 billion. All quarters responsible for settling this problem have to see the question comprehensively as it concerns not only debts but our self-respect, which has been damaged by certain people or groups who want the country to collapse. Of course, we must not give up on this challenge, no matter how great it is. However, the government should realize that the people keep on watching this development. They have been clamoring for the settlement of this problem. - Republika. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010709dx5f002g6\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
