\par\par \b \uc2  Broadening the  \highlight22\uc2 tax \highlight\uc2  base. \b0\par\par\uc2 739 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Easing the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden is, theoretically, one of the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  instruments usually employed by a government to reinvigorate a slumping \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The rationale is that a lighter \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden will increase the amount of disposable income of taxpayers, thereby bolstering their purchasing power and consequently strengthening private consumption so as to encourage \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity. \par \par \uc2  This popular line of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reasoning should be quite relevant to Indonesia as its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is projected to be 1.5 to two percentage points lower than the original estimate of four percent to five percent made at the outset of the 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year in January. Such a populist program would also be quite attractive as a political instrument for a government like that of Abdurrahman Wahid whose popularity and credibility is declining sharply. \par \par \uc2  The government is nonetheless being compelled to pursue the unpopular measure of stepping up its \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection campaign, which in many other countries would be the surest path to political suicide. In fact, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and excise duties are one of the five main \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  instruments being employed by the government to raise additional revenue so as to cover its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which for the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year is estimated to be about Rp 30 trillion (US$2.7 billion) larger than the original projection of Rp 53 trillion. \par \par \uc2  There are, however, several factors and conditions in Indonesia that still allow for a more concerted \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  effort without causing more suffering for the people at large, who have been groaning under the strain of severe \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  hardship since the crisis broke out in late 1997. \par \par \uc2  First of all, the government will focus its \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  campaign on direct \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , notably income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Even in this sector, the main objective is to broaden the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  base, not to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates, by registering potential taxpayers who have hitherto remained outside the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  net. Different from indirect \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  which squarely hit all taxpayers irrespective of their income levels, the impact of direct \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  is discriminative in that the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate is progressive in line with the level of income. \par \par \uc2  Most studies by domestic and international analysts have concluded that there are still tremendous opportunities for raising income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues in the country due to massive \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  evasion and the high incidence of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  fraud. The incidence of noncompliance in respect of personal and corporate income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been estimated at 50 percent. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  directorate general recently validated the conclusion of the studies, disclosing that only around one million of the country's 210 million people have been issued with personal \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  identification numbers. Worse still, only about 50 percent of this small number actually file annual income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns. \par \par \uc2  The number is certainly quite small even though it does not include several million paid employees who pay their income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  through their employers (pay-as-you-earn system). \par \par \uc2  The government, therefore, is quite justified in stepping up its effort to register more potential taxpayers. Given its recent success in netting hundreds of potential taxpayers in the elite Pondok Indah residential area in South Jakarta, the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office is expected to stage similarly vigorous campaigns in other high-income residential areas not only in the capital city but also other major cities throughout the country. \par \par \uc2  However, simply registering potential taxpayers will not automatically raise \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues if the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration system is not capable of detecting all the income actually received, both from within the country and from overseas, by taxpayers. In this connection, we think, the government needs to improve the mechanisms whereby \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials are authorized to cross-check information on taxpayers' incomes and expenditures in cooperation with other institutions such as banks, the electricity and telecommunications companies, and the motor vehicle registration office. \par \par \uc2  But law enforcement, though necessary to minimize \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  evasion and \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  fraud, is not sufficient to ensure \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  compliance as there will never be enough \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  auditors to examine all taxpayers. \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  compliance involves the willingness of taxpayers to pay \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and this, in turn, is influenced partly by their perception of the integrity of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials and the government's credibility in general. Efficient and transparent \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration is also crucial for minimizing the cost of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  compliance. Taxpayers will be discouraged from registering if their \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  identification numbers make them subject to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  concerning questions of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law, and costly objections, appeals and \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 -rebate procedures. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5f000n0\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
