\par\par \b \uc2  Government warned negative spread a threat to banks. \b0\par\par\uc2 617 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  finance committee warned the government on Monday to immediately seek a solution to the negative spread problem threatening some of the country's major banks. \par \par \uc2  Benny Pasaribu, the chairman of House Commission IX for financial and development planning affairs, said on Monday that the negative spread problem could erode banks' capital adequacy ratio (CAR) which in turn might force the government to spend more taxpayers money on recapitalizing the banks once again. \par \par \uc2  "We have information that some banks are suffering from negative spread problems which may erode their CAR," Benny told reporters following an internal meeting. \par \par \uc2  "We'll summon the finance minister and IBRA on Thursday to discuss strategies to resolve the problem ... We want to know the details," he added. \par \par \uc2  Several bankers had earlier expressed concerns that their banks would suffer negative spread problems due to continuing increases in \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark interest rate. \par \par \uc2  Bankers said that the increasing benchmark rate was putting upward pressure on the time deposit rate, but unfortunately the banks could not pass this on through new lending with higher \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  due to the still high risk attached to the country's real sector. These conditions were triggering the negative spread problem. \par \par \uc2  The problem is much greater in banks which hold a larger proportion of government bonds carrying a fixed interest rate of 12.5 percent as these banks' main source of revenue is still the interest on government bonds. \par \par \uc2  The government has issued a massive Rp 430 trillion worth of bonds to recapitalize around 27 banks. The bonds carry fixed and variable rates linked to the interest rate on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  SBI promissory notes. But some of the recapitalized banks, including the huge Bank Mandiri, Bank Danamon, Bank Negara Indonesia and Bank Rakyat Indonesia, accepted a greater proportion of fixed rate bonds. \par \par \uc2  In a bid to avoid the negative spread problem, some banks had reportedly made a deal to keep the interest rate on time deposits unchanged, but it did not succeed. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has continued to increase the interest rate on its one-month SBI notes over the past couple of months in a bid to help curb the inflationary threat and defend the ailing rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The one-month SBI rate is currently at 16.26 percent. Although deposit rates of some banks are still lower than the SBI rate, the banks cannot fully take advantage of this by investing all their funds in the notes because the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  only offers the notes in very limited amounts. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah dropped to a 31-month low of more than Rp 12,000 per U.S. dollar last month due to a combination of domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  woes. \par \par \uc2  But although the rupiah managed to strengthen to near the Rp 11,000 per dollar level last week, top \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials have said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would maintain its tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  until expectations of high inflation had receded. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Miranda Goeltom recently said that inflationary pressure was high as reflected in the year-on-year inflation rate of around 10 percent over the past few months. \par \par \uc2  The government has called on the independent \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to stop increasing the interest rate to avoid greater state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  expenses. The state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  covers the interest cost of the bank recapitalization bonds. \par \par \uc2  Every one percent increase in the SBI rate causes additional \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  expenses of around Rp 2.5 trillion, finance minister Prijadi Praptosuhardjo has said. \par \par \uc2  The rising SBI rate has become one of the factors forcing the government to revise the current 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5f000nh\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  ' \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  recovery hampered by  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties \highlight\uc2 '. \b0\par\par\uc2 238 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 May 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Indonesia is facing signs of slowing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  recovery due \par \par \uc2  to a number of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , said the Finance Minister. According to \par \par \uc2  Finance Minister Prijadi Praptosuhardjo, the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  are caused by \par \par \uc2  political, securities and order instabilities, and lack of law enforcement \par \par \uc2  and raw decentralization process. He warned the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors could \par \par \uc2  hamper the people's welfare if they are not immediately dealt with. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  have played dominant role in slowing the recovery process," \par \par \uc2  said Prijadi yesterday. \par \par \uc2  According to him, Indonesia cannot solve problems it is currently facing \par \par \uc2  amid rapid fundamental changes. But hoped that the problems can be reduced \par \par \uc2  in the future. \par \par \uc2  "We can handle the problems gradually if we are consistent with the \par \par \uc2  policies \par \par \uc2  and agreements we made," he said. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is predicted to return to its pre-crisis recovery level \par \par \uc2  in 2004 if this year's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth reaches 3.5% and grows at an \par \par \uc2  average \par \par \uc2  of 5% to 6% in the next three years, said an official. \par \par \uc2  Finance Minister Prijadi Praptosuhardjo said Indonesia could catch up with \par \par \uc2  its neighboring countries if it could retain the growth target. Meanwhile, \par \par \uc2  if the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  only grows at an average of 3% per year, Indonesia would \par \par \uc2  need \par \par \uc2  6 to 7 years to return to its pre-crisis level, he said. \par \par \uc2  "And if the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  continue to prevail, we might be trapped into a \par \par \uc2  deeper crisis," he said at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . (01/ab). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010710dx5g000ph\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
