\par\par \b \uc2  Prijadi sees 5-6% annual GDP growth in 2002-2004. \b0\par\par\uc2 565 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Finance minister Prijadi Praptosuhardjo said on Tuesday that the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could grow by between 5 and 6 percent per year between 2002 and 2004, up from an estimated 3.5 percent in 2001. \par \par \uc2  But Prijadi said that such stronger \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth would only materialize if the current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  could be gradually eliminated. \par \par \uc2  "If this year we can register 3.5 percent growth, and over the next three years the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  can grow by an average of 5 percent to 6 percent per annum, then by 2004 the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will have recovered to its pre-crisis condition," he said in a speech at a plenary session of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  held to start the debating process on the government-proposed 2002 annual development plan. \par \par \uc2  "However, if (the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) only grows by an average of 3 percent per year, then we will need between 6 and 7 years to return to pre-crisis conditions. In fact, if the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  drags on, we could tumble into an even deeper crisis," he added. \par \par \uc2  "Right now, we're facing signs of a slower \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery ... the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  factor is playing a dominant role in causing this slower recovery." \par \par \uc2  Prijadi emphasized that the current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  was the result of domestic political instability, security problems, a weak legal system, and poor implementation of the regional autonomy and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  decentralization programs. \par \par \uc2  "... the problems cannot be overcome quickly. But looking forward, we expect the problems can be gradually resolved ... at least the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  can be reduced," he said. \par \par \uc2  The main source of the current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been the crisis of leadership as the embattled President Abdurrahman Wahid seems to have lost credibility following the recent issuance of a second censure by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  which may lead to the initiation of an impeachment process. \par \par \uc2  Some legislators have upped the ante in their efforts to force Abdurrahman to step down so as to allow the popular Vice President, Megawati Soekarnoputri, to take charge of the country. \par \par \uc2  Several economists have said that the immediate resignation of Abdurrahman or the delegation of more power to Megawati would help resolve the national leadership crisis. \par \par \uc2  Reports said that Abdurrahman continued to search for a political compromise, although many believe that such a prospect is dim to say the least. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis that started in the middle of 1997 has hit the country badly with gross domestic product (GDP) contracting by nearly 14 percent in 1998 forcing many companies and banks to the wall and leading to a record level of unemployment. The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis also helped to oust former authoritarian president Soeharto from power. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  managed to grow at a surprisingly frisky 4.8 percent in 2000, led primarily by strong domestic consumption and exports. \par \par \uc2  But due to the current political turbulence at home, the government has to cut back the GDP forecast for this year to 3.5 percent, compared to earlier projections of around 5 percent. \par \par \uc2  Achieving pre-crisis level \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is seen as crucial in order to absorb the huge number of unemployed, which, according to the govenrment totaled more than 38 million people out of the country's more than 200 million population. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was growing at a rate of more than 7 percent prior to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis.(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5g000ns\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
