\par\par \b \uc2  HABIBIE CENTER CALLS FOR STOP TO POLITICAL  \highlight22\uc2 UNCERTAINTY \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 430 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 May 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited.< Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its\par \par \uc2  Jakarta, May 18 (ANTARA) - The Habibie Center, a non-profit organization named after former president BJ Habibie, has called on the country's national components to soon stop the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  currently prevailing in the affairs of state. One of the Center's executives, Watik Pratikya, disclosed during a press conference entitled "Weighing the Future of the Nation" at the Habibie Center building here on Friday that the leadership crisis has reached its top because President Abdurrahman Wahid has lost his moral and social legitimacy to govern. Meanwhile, he said, the president's lack of understanding on the presidency's dependence on \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  support has further worsened the political crisis. According to Pratikya, without the support of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , where President Wahid controls only 11 percent of the seats, it would be impossible for the president to be effective in his job. \par \par \uc2   "However, it should be born in mind that, while the leadership change is important, it will not suffice in itself," Pratikya observed. He reiterated that leadership change would be necessary, but that whoever takes over the leadership, he or she should as soon as possible take some important steps to overcome the multi-dimensional crisis. "It's true that the main cause of the present political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  is the leadership crisis. So, a leadership change has become an urgent necessity," he said. In addition to calling for a stop to the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the Habibie Center also demanded that a few short-term measures - which include \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, the restoration of a sense of peace among the people, and the promotion of the quality of security authorities - be promptly undertaken. "But, we would like to stress that the Habibie Center is not seeking to impose itself. This is only a contribution of thoughts," said Fanny Habibie, another executive of the Center. Fanny, who is a younger brother to BJ Habibie, pointed out further that the Center offered the contribution because of its concern over the fate of the nation. Meanwhile, speaking about medium-term and long-term projection, the Habibie Center suggested to carry out five main programs. First, reinvigorating the people's common commitment for the birth and survival of the Republic of Indonesia. Secondly, consolidating democracy. Thirdly, redeveloping a just and fair relation between the central government and the regions. Fourthly, recapturing the momentum for the national development. And fifthly, restoring Indonesia's good image in the international world. The press conference was attended, among others, by Indria Samego and some other executives of the Center. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010709dx5i002u1\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
