\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  outlook remains gloomy despite 2.6% growth. \b0\par\par\uc2 845 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Although \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the first quarter of this year fulfilled the market's expectations, many economists warn that the outlook for the rest of the year is much more gloomy. \par \par \uc2  They said that unless the current domestic political instability was resolved, 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth might be even lower than the government's new target of around 3.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  "I'm pessimistic that the government's growth target can be met if the current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  are not eliminated," Gadjah Mada University economist Sri Adiningsih said. \par \par \uc2  The Central Bureau of Statistics reported on Friday that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew by 2.6 percent in the first quarter of this year from the fourth quarter of last year, mainly due to rapid growth in the agricultural sector. \par \par \uc2  Danareksa Research Institute chief economist Raden Pardede said that growth in the agricultural sector was seasonal, and a slowdown was expected in the coming months as the harvest period ended. \par \par \uc2  "What we need to see now is how the manufacturing sector will perform," he said, adding that it had been considered one of the main factors driving the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He explained that since growth in the manufacturing sector last year was mainly driven by exports, the sector would likely perform poorly with the expected \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdowns in the U.S. and Japan, two of Indonesia's most important traditional export markets. \par \par \uc2  He added that new investments, particularly in durable goods, could not be expected given the current domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He said that with the prospect of a severe state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government could not be expected to provide any new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "So, looking at the demand side, both domestic and external, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will be slower in the second and third quarters," Raden said. \par \par \uc2  "Our (\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth) forecast for the full year is 2.8 percent to 3 percent," he added. \par \par \uc2  If compared with the January-March period of last year, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in this year's first quarter was 4.1 percent, within the government's target. But the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the investment climate and the gloomy outlook in the country could cause a slowdown in overall \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity in the coming months. \par \par \uc2  Sri Adiningsih said investment and exports, which were the main engines driving the country's 4.8 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth last year, would make a lower contribution to this year's gross domestic product (GDP). \par \par \uc2  After a sharp \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  contraction of about 14 percent in 1998, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  managed to register relatively flat growth in 1999 and a stronger-than-expected 4.8 percent growth in 2000. \par \par \uc2  But the country is now losing this \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  momentum as political instability scares off investors and sends the rupiah tumbling and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  soaring. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have warned that it is crucial for the country to register minimum \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 3.5 percent this year. They say this is necessary to provide a sufficient basis for higher growth in the coming years, to help absorb the massive number of unemployed and to avoid a new round of social unrest. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Finance Prijadi Praptosuhardjo told legislators early last week that if the country's current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  could at least be overcome gradually, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could grow by 3.5 percent this year and by an average of 5 percent to 6 percent from 2002 to 2004. \par \par \uc2  But he warned that if the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  dragged on, Indonesia could tumble into a deeper crisis. \par \par \uc2  Embattled President Abdurrahman Wahid has been facing growing calls to resign and hand over power to his popular Vice President, Megawati Soekarnoputri. Particularly strident in calling for Abdurrahman's resignation have been legislators, who recently issued a second censure against the President for his alleged involvement in two financial scandals. \par \par \uc2  The political fate of Abdurrahman may be decided in August, when the People's Consultative Assembly, the country's top law-making body, may convene a special session to begin impeachment proceedings against him. \par \par \uc2  The sharp drop in the rupiah and soaring domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  may cause the 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to widen to a critical 6 percent of GDP, compared with the initial projection of 3.7 percent of GDP. \par \par \uc2  The government recently announced plans to raise fuel prices by an average of 30 percent, electricity rates by 20 percent and value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  by 2.5 percent in a bid to limit the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to the safer level of 3.7 percent of GDP. \par \par \uc2  The House has yet to approve the plan. And some observers fear these hikes, particularly the increase in fuel prices, could trigger social unrest if the government fails to win \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  support for the move and insulate the poor from the brunt of the impact of this new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Several businesspeople said earlier these price hikes could send more companies into bankruptcy, with many businesses already suffering under recent increases in fuel prices and power rates, as well as the sharp drop in the rupiah and rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5l005g6\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
