uirement, further testing the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  resolve. \par \par \uc2  S & P said the government's heavy debts, including those to the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and bank recapitalization bonds, estimated to peak at about 90 percent of GDP at the end of 2001, could rise further depending on the exchange rate and other variables. \par \par \uc2  It said the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector's net external debt, expected to peak at about 60 percent of current account receipts at the end of 2001, generates an onerous amortization profile with over US$8 billion due each year in the period between 2001 and 2005. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  financing continue as \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  disruptions have prompted key multilateral and bilateral creditors to cut back on new and existing loan commitments, widening the financial gap, the agency added. \par \par \uc2  "With the determined implementation of upcoming \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revisions, Indonesia could reverse such a process and secure further Paris Club loans rescheduling them for next year; with weak implementation, it could relapse into an inflationary spiral," the agency said. \par \par \uc2  S & P said that the first scenario could include further, isolated syndicated loan defaults; the second could include a general sovereign default. \par \par \uc2  It said that the negative outlook reflects expectations that \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  disruption will persist at least until current preliminary proceedings to impeach President Abdurrahman Wahid have run their course. \par \par \uc2  Additionally, political commitment to primary \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  surpluses of between 3 percent and 4 percent of GDP - at the consolidated general government level - and divestment proceeds of between 2 percent and 3 percent of GDP, will be central to Indonesia's sovereign debt-management strategy and credit standing, the agency said. \par \par \uc2  "Indonesia's capacity to deliver such \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  results is doubtful," it concluded. (hen) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5m005lg\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
