\par\par \b \uc2  Parties doubtful of Gus Dur's impeachment. \b0\par\par\uc2 771 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): With support aplenty for a People's Consultative Assembly special session to impeach President Abdurrahman Wahid, a top official of the National Awakening Party (PKB) faction in the Assembly says signs of apprehension are visible among the power brokers over whether to proceed with the constitutional move. \par \par \uc2  Chairman of the PKB faction, Yusuf Muhammad, told the media at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  building on Tuesday that even major factions like the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan) and Golkar were \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the prospect of an MPR special session. \par \par \uc2  "All political forces are anxious to move ahead to the special session. We, therefore, call for a settlement to the nation's problems though political compromise," Yusuf said. \par \par \uc2  The PKB was founded by Abdurrahman, who is now the party's chief patron. \par \par \uc2  Yusuf said that PDI Perjuangan, despite its leading role, was half-hearted about the move to haul Abdurrahman before an MPR special session. \par \par \uc2  "They're still not certain that they'll be able to resolve the crisis facing the nation after assuming power. Besides, they are still traumatized by the Axis Force maneuver," Yusuf said. \par \par \uc2  The Axis Force, a loose coalition of Muslim parties, catapulted Abdurrahman to the presidency at Megawati's expense in 1999, but now staunchly supports her elevation to the top executive job in place of Abdurrahman. \par \par \uc2  Yusuf said Golkar also "feels secure" under Abdurrahman, because he allows the party to have a say in both the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  field and the bureaucracy. \par \par \uc2  The Axis Force, according to Yusuf, will be facing a split when it comes to the question of the vice presidency should Megawati take over the reins of power from Abdurrahman. \par \par \uc2  "Therefore, an (Assembly) special session is just a way to solve the problems and not the solution itself. There is a chance of reaching political compromises," Yusuf said. \par \par \uc2  Separately, the moves of House faction leaders to convene a special session in order to produce an effective government gained more support, with the United Development Party (PPP) calling for an accelerated special session. \par \par \uc2  Hamzah Haz, the chairman of PPP, said his party fully accepted the conclusion reached by House faction leaders that Abdurrahman's government had lost the support of the majority of political parties and that an effective government was urgently needed to defuse the protracted crisis. \par \par \uc2  He was speaking after a two-hour meeting with leaders of five factions at the PPP headquarters here on Tuesday afternoon. \par \par \uc2  The faction leaders were Arifin Panigoro of PDI Perjuangan, Syamsul Muarif of Golkar, Alimarwan Hanan of PPP, Hatta Radjasa of the National Mandate Party (PAN) and Amiruddin Djaja Subita of the Ummat Sovereignty Party (PDU). \par \par \uc2  The faction leaders had previously met with Yuzril Ihza Mahendra, chairman of the Crescent Star Party (PBB), and Amien Rais, the chairman of PAN. Both figures pledged their support for a special session to overcome the political crisis. \par \par \uc2  Arifin, who acted as spokesman for the faction leaders, said they would soon meet with Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri, Golkar chairman Akbar Tandjung, and Indonesian Military commander Admiral Widodo Adi Sutjipto. \par \par \uc2  The faction leaders reiterated that they preferred a special session as a constitutional way of resolving the political deadlock, rather than a Cabinet reshuffle based on the parties' representation in the House. \par \par \uc2  "The President recently offered a political compromise but the major parties have given it the cold shoulder," said Syamsul. \par \par \uc2  Arifin dismissed a political compromise, saying the main problem was not the cabinet but the President himself. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, PDI Perjuangan gave a strong signal on Tuesday that they would support a special session, saying that the President had yet to response to the second House censure. \par \par \uc2  Kwik Kian Gie, a senior party member, said after a meeting with Megawati at her official residence that the President had ignored the two memorandums of censure served on him. \par \par \uc2  "If the President provides a satisfactory response then it will stop, but if the reply is disappointing, there will be no other option than a special session," he said. \par \par \uc2  In Surabaya, East Java, a number of mass organizations that claimed to be affiliated to PDI Perjuangan stated their opposition to the proposed special session and threatened to sever their ties with the party if their protests were ignored. \par \par \uc2  The organizations, grouped under the umbrella of the People's Sovereignty Unity Front (Sakera), had around one million supporters, coordinator of the movement Supriyanto claimed on Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  He further asserted that he did not believe Megawati had given support for a special session to impeach President Abdurrahman Wahid. (rms/dja/emf/nur) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5n005mw\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
