\par\par \b \uc2  Summitplast to open third plastics factory next month. \b0\par\par\uc2 599 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  10 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Publicly listed plastic component producer PT Summitplast Interbenua will commence next month the operation of its third factory at its industrial compound in the Lippo Cikarang industrial estate in West Java. \par \par \uc2  Summitplast president Dhani Sutanto said here on Wednesday the new plant, which will have a production capacity of 4,000 metric tons, would boost the company's total production by 15 percent to 32,000 metric tons a year. \par \par \uc2  "The plant will enable us to meet the growing demand from the Asia Pacific, mainly came from Japan and the U.S.," he said following the company's general shareholders meeting. \par \par \uc2  Dhani added that the company spent about Rp 40 billion (US$ 3.6 million), most of it raised from the its initial \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offering last year, to build the new factory. \par \par \uc2  Currently, Summitplast, a joint venture of two Japanese firms and two Indonesian companies, operates two factories, one in Lippo Cikarang, Bekasi, and another in Tangerang, with total production of 28,000 tons per annum. \par \par \uc2  The company exports 95 percent of its products to electronic home appliance manufacturers and automotive companies. \par \par \uc2  Dhani said the completion of the new plant would help the company meet its sales target this year. \par \par \uc2  According to him, the company expects a 20 percent increase in revenue this year from Rp 170 billion last year. \par \par \uc2  "We also estimate that our pretax profit will increase by 15 percent from Rp 22.3 billion in 2000," he said. \par \par \uc2  Dhani added that realized revenue between January and April surged 65 percent to Rp 52 billion, while pretax profit in the same period increased by 40 percent to Rp 17 billion, compared to the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  "We continued to receive high demand during the period ... we also took advantage of the weakening rupiah," he said, adding that the company's products were sold based on the US dollar. \par \par \uc2  However, he said, the company would maintain its original revenue targets because the country's ongoing political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  could affect the company's performance. \par \par \uc2  He said, for example, that if the country's security situation continued to weaken it would endanger the company's exports. \par \par \uc2  During the meeting, the shareholders approved the company's plan to pay a total of Rp 5.8 billion in dividends, or Rp 35 per share. \par \par \uc2  The shareholders also agreed to the proposed one-to-five stock split in a bid to improve the quality of the company's share trading. Under the proposal, each of the company's shares, with a par value of Rp 500, will divided into five shares, each carrying a nominal value of Rp 100. \par \par \uc2  The shareholders also agreed to changes in the composition of the supervisory board and the board of executives. \par \par \uc2  The new supervisory board is led by Soebekti Hambali as the chief commissioner. The other three members of the board are Amir Kosasih, Masa-aki Uemura, who replaces Hironori Kato, and Slamet Singgih. \par \par \uc2  Uemura is currently deputy general manager of the chemical and plastics division at Sumitomo Corp. in Tokyo, while Slamet occupies an expert staff position at the Ministry of Energy and Mineral Resources. \par \par \uc2  Dhani Sutanto will continue to serve as company president, with Tirtadjaja Hambali as finance director, Johannes Jali as operational director, Hidenori Yamada as marketing director, replacing Yojiro Ishibashi, and Naoki Hanabusa as production director, replacing Hideto Omatsu. \par \par \uc2  Yamada is also general manager of Sumitomo Shoji Plastic Co. Ltd., while Omatsu is general manager of the chemical and plastics division at Sumitomo Corp. (05) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5p005o4\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
