\par\par \b \uc2  WB proposes 3 measures to maintain recovery. \b0\par\par\uc2 908 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The World Bank has outlined three immediate actions the Indonesian government must implement to maintain the momentum of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in 2001, given the current political instability. \par \par \uc2  World Bank country director Mark Baird said here on Wednesday that the three measures included restoring budgetary discipline as soon as possible, implementing the decentralization program in a fair and transparent manner, and pressing ahead with the restructuring and sales of assets under the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA). \par \par \uc2  "What is needed to maintain the recovery in 2001? Well, I could say the obvious is that all you need is political stability, law and order, and a functioning court system... But while that's all very important to investors, I think we also recognize that's not part of the short-term outlook," Baird told a business luncheon organized by the Mercantile Club Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  "So the real question is what can you do, given there's political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and given we won't have a smoothly functioning judicial system for quite sometime ... There's a lot that can be done to improve the current situation ... I would like to focus on three key short-term issues," he added. \par \par \uc2  While the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  expanded with a higher-than-expected growth of 4.8 percent in 2000, there have been signs that growth in 2001 will be much slower than initially expected due to domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the prospect of an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown in the USA. \par \par \uc2  Baird said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  adjustment package unveiled by the government last week in a bid to limit the 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to a reasonable level of around 3.7 percent of gross domestic product (GDP) was a sensible and sound proposal. \par \par \uc2  "The package proposed by the Cabinet last week makes a lot of sense, although it remains to be seen whether the legislature will be able to approve it quickly so that the government can move ahead with its implementation," he said. \par \par \uc2  The 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  could widen to a dangerous level of around 6 percent of GDP, primarily due to the sharp plunge in the value of the rupiah and rising domestic interest rate. \par \par \uc2  To avoid the risk of a \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  catastrophe, the government proposed a \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  adjustment package focusing on three bold measures: a further reduction in \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on fuel and electricity through raising fuel prices by an average 30 percent and power rates by 20 percent, raising value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  to 12.5 percent from the current 10 percent level, and a more efficient transfer of central government funds to provincial and district administrations. \par \par \uc2  Baird said the government could no longer borrow any more to contain the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  indebtedness had already soared to 100 percent of GDP, while at the same time a further \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  cut on basic infrastructure and social services could lead Indonesia into a major crisis over these items in the future. \par \par \uc2  "To solve this (\b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) problem you cannot borrow more. That's my proposition. Nor can you afford to really cap development \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  further more," he said, pointing out that the \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  cut had already been significant in recent years. \par \par \uc2  He also said that with one-third of central government revenue being transferred to local government as a consequence of the new \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  decentralization program, "this leaves very little room for the government to adjust to adverse macroeconomic development." \par \par \uc2  "So the government is focusing on other options: higher \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , lower fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and more efficient transfer to the regions," he said. \par \par \uc2  "All of these are politically difficult and all of them of course have their own impact on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . So I think we have great sympathy for the task ahead for the government on how to bring the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  down to a more reasonable level," he added. \par \par \uc2  Baird said that on the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  decentralization program, the concern was over its implementation. \par \par \uc2  "But we have to acknowledge that it has not been as bad as many had feared a year ago," he said, pointing out that the government had taken steps to bar regional government from borrowing this year. \par \par \uc2  But he said that there were still some issues, including concern over regional government aggressively reimposing local \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regulations that had been simplified in recent years, and over the impact of uncoordinated decisions at the local level that affected the environment. \par \par \uc2  On the issue of IBRA, Baird said that it was important for IBRA to be able to realize its cash target of Rp 27 trillion to help finance the 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He also gave a warning about the importance of the quality of the corporate restructuring work carried out by IBRA in a bid to revive investor confidence and limit the government's burden. \par \par \uc2  "We are very pleased with the new corporate debt restructuring principles that have been adopted by (the government). They lay out a transparent process of independent review for the largest debtors," he said. \par \par \uc2  "We recognized that debt restructuring is an inherently political process and the principles will not always be followed in practice, but at least there will be a clear set of principles against which decisions will have to be explained and justified and hopefully this will allow the process to move ahead more rapidly and in a less controversial manner because it is essential that IBRA achieve its cash recovery target in 2001," he added. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx5p005ob\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
