\par\par \b \uc2  PDI-P MEMBER CALLS FOR EARLY SPECIAL MPR SESSION. \b0\par\par\uc2 400 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 May 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited.< Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its\par \par \uc2  Jakarta, May 31 (ANTARA) - A senior member of the Indonesian Democratic Party - Struggle (PDI-P) has called for an earlier-than-scheduled special session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) to ask for President Abdurrahman Wahid's accountability. "Why do we have to wait for two months? Why not (hold it) next week? This will lead to an \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil which would eventually add to the people's sufferings," Aberson Marle Sihaloho said here Thursday. To hold the special session, the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR) only need to invite MPR members from the interest group and the regional group because the House legislators are automatically MPR members, he said. "So, if the special MPR session is held next week, we only need to wait for the arrival of the MPR members from the regional group and the interest group. \par \par \uc2   What is more, the special session will have a single agenda, to ask for the president's accountability for violating Article 9 of the 1945 Constitution, as accused by the House," he said. House Speaker Akbar Tanjung said on Wednesday that based on official procedure, the assembly's working committee will make preparations for the special session in the next two months. In the special session, the president is expected to be asked to present his response to the House's memorandum of censure, which stipulates that he has violated his oath and the assembly decree on clean governance due to his alleged involvement in two financial scandals. Aberson said if the president's accountability report is rejected, it will be for the MPR to decide "whether he will be given a chance or replaced directly". Since the agenda of the special MPR session is simple, the MPR working committee need not occupy itself with preparing a draft resolution on the matter for a long time, he said. Whatever happens in the forthcoming special MPR session is up to the MPR members because it is they and not the House factions who will have to vote individually, he said. A total of 365 legislators on Wednesday voted in favor of the MPR session to impeach the president, 4 rejected it and 39 abstained. Some 51 legislators from the Nation's Awakening Party (PKB), which the president helped found, defiantly boycotted the proceedings by walking out of the meeting. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010709dx5v002g2\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
