\par\par \b \uc2  Special session to be held on Aug. 1. \b0\par\par\uc2 727 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 June 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Indonesians can expect to know by the second week of August if they will be swearing in their third president in two years, or whether a political compromise has been struck to extend the life of President Abdurrahman Wahid's administration. \par \par \uc2  The valuation comes after legislators set Aug. 1 as the date for the start of the special session of the People's Consultative Assembly to demand Abdurrahman to present a presidential accountability to the country's highest institution. \par \par \uc2  The special session is expected to last seven or eight days. \par \par \uc2  Assembly speaker Amien Rais said the schedule was set after a consultation meeting between the Assembly leadership and the Assembly's faction leaders here on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  "The Assembly will stick to the Constitution in preparing the special session. It will be held two months after it is recommended by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said, referring to the 1978 and 2000 Assembly Decrees on the special session. \par \par \uc2  After the House voted overwhelmingly in favor of calling for a special session late on Wednesday, the House's secretary-general Sri Sumarjati officially handed on Thursday morning the recommendations to Assembly leaders here. \par \par \uc2  According to Amien, that Assembly's working committee would hold a meeting on Friday to continue preparations, including drafting the special session's agenda. \par \par \uc2  Amien would not speculate on whether a hastened schedule would be discussed, but instead repeated that they would stick with the timeframe stipulated within the decrees. \par \par \uc2  However the possibility of an accelerated special session, probably within 72-hours, was still open, should drastic developments, such as the imposition of a state of emergency, arise. \par \par \uc2  Amien remarked that the Annual Assembly, usually held in August, would likely be postponed until September or October. \par \par \uc2  Matori Abdul Djalil, deputy Assembly speaker and chairman of the National Awakening Party (PKB), maintained that despite the faction's walk-out during Wednesday's vote at the House, the party accepted the House's decision and would take part in the special session. \par \par \uc2  Matori said the PKB faction in the Assembly would intensify its lobby with other factions in an endeavor to seek a political compromise in the special session. \par \par \uc2  Separately, presidential spokesman Yahya C. Staquf criticized House factions for political indecency by forcing the nation to convene a special session. \par \par \uc2  "Politicians have put aside political decency as they have taken a political step that is unlawful," he said. \par \par \uc2  Yahya regretted that the House ignored the result of the Attorney General's Office's investigation into the two \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  scandals that cleared the President of any involvement. \par \par \uc2  In Yogyakarta, Ichlasul Amal, a political analyst of Gadjah Mada University, said the Attorney General's findings could not be used as the basis for rejecting a special session. \par \par \uc2  He argued that the problem at hand was not merely the question of the scandals but also his controversial leadership. \par \par \uc2  He believed the President still has a chance to survive if his camp intensify their lobby for a political compromise with major parties. \par \par \uc2  Separately, certain legislators here were already calling for a hastened special session. \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle's (PDI Perjuangan) Marle Aberson Sihaloho said there was no point waiting for two months, while leaving the people in a state of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "It's unreasonable, unconstitutional and inefficient to wait until August because 500 of the 700 Assembly members are already in Jakarta and the session will have a single-item agenda of asking the president's accountability," he said. \par \par \uc2  According to him, the special session could be held by next week, having to wait only for the remaining 200 members of the Societal Groups and Regional Representatives factions, a majority of whom are already in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the Supreme Advisory Council (DPA) called for a solution to the leadership crisis as a preliminary requirement for national reconciliation. \par \par \uc2  "The leadership crisis must be settled first before national reconciliation is promoted in a move to overcome the continued political crisis," Achmad Tirto Sudiro, DPA chairman, said after meeting with Coordinating Minister for Political, Social and Security Affairs Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono here on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  He stated that DPA had recently suggested the President be "non-active" for health reasons and delegate his power to Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri but so far, he has yet to respond. (rms) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx61000t5\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
