\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty \highlight\uc2  could affect  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2  - BI. \b0\par\par\uc2 711 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 June 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin warned on Thursday that the basic macroeconomic assumptions used in the revised 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not be realistic if political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country continued throughout the rest of the year. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said that the proposed new \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions were considered "realistic," only on the assumption that political conditions improved significantly in the second half of this year. \par \par \uc2  "If the (political) situation does not improve significantly, I'm not sure whether the assumptions can be met," he told the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  task force during a meeting. \par \par \uc2  The government has proposed to the House a revision of the January-December 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , following the recent sharp plunge in the exchange rate of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar, and rising domestic interest rate. \par \par \uc2  Under the proposed revision, the average rupiah exchange rate is set at Rp 9,600 per U.S. dollar (compared with an earlier assumption of Rp 7,800 per dollar), inflation rate 9.3 percent (7.2 percent), and interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  3-month SBI promissory notes at 15 percent (11.5 percent). \par \par \uc2  The drop in the value of the rupiah has been partly due to ongoing political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as embattled President Abdurrahman Wahid has been under strong pressure from the House to step down and hand over power to the popular Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri. \par \par \uc2  The country's top legislature, the People's Consultative Assembly, will hold a special session in early August that could result in the impeachment of the President. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Achjar Iljas said that in order for the exchange rate assumption of 9,600 per dollar to be realized, the average exchange rate over the next seven months would need to be at around Rp 9,300 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  "The exchange rate of the rupiah has been affected by not only \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but also non-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors, particularly politics and security. So if these factors do not improve significantly, it's difficult to expect an average exchange rate of Rp 9,600 per dollar," Achjar said. \par \par \uc2  The average exchange rate of the rupiah during the first five months was around Rp 10,342 per dollar. The rupiah closed at Rp 11,160 per dollar late on Thursday, slightly higher than its rate of Rp 11,210 on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  The exchange rate of the rupiah is also closely linked to the inflation rate, as the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is highly dependent on imported raw materials. If the rupiah drops, inflation will increase (due to higher import costs), thus pushing interest rate further upward. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Miranda Goeltom said that amid the current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would maintain its tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  However, Miranda added that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would loosen its monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  if the political situation improved in the second half of this year. \par \par \uc2  She said that the interest rate on 1-month SBI notes could increase to almost 17 percent by August, given the current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The benchmark interest rate is currently hovering at 16.38 percent. \par \par \uc2  But Miranda added that if the political situation improved, the benchmark interest rate could fall to around 15 percent, allowing the interest rate on 3-month SBI notes to go down to 14 percent - 16 percent, in line with the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  target. \par \par \uc2  When asked by legislators to define what \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  meant by "improvements in the political situation", Sjahril said, "It's difficult to say exactly, because it's a relative thing. What's important is a significant improvement that could increase market confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  Some legislators had said earlier that the resignation of Abdurrahman could improve the political situation. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Sjahril said that the interest rate assumption of 15 percent was already realistic. \par \par \uc2  He said that if the interest rate assumption were lowered, as demanded by some legislators, the financial market would deem it non-realistic. \par \par \uc2  Miranda warned that if the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions were not realistic, the rupiah could immediately tumble, as when the government proposed the 1998/99 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  with grossly unrealistic assumptions. The rupiah then immediately tumbled to Rp 7,000 per dollar from Rp 5,000.(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx68000zw\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picsc