\par\par \b \uc2  Fuel price hike impact 'greater than expected'. \b0\par\par\uc2 664 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 June 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The weekend fuel price increase could have a greater impact on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  than the government has anticipated, particularly amid the current social and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , experts warned. \par \par \uc2  Economist Umar Juoro said that the fuel price increase would send inflation higher than projected which would in turn further erode consumer purchasing power. \par \par \uc2  "It (the fuel price increase) will create a greater burden on the people and will also cause a slowdown in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity," Umar said on Sunday. \par \par \uc2  The government raised fuel prices by an average of 30 percent on Saturday as part of measures to help limit the widening 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to a safer level. The government will also raise electricity rates by more than 17 percent early next month. \par \par \uc2  Srijanto Tjokro Sudarmo, an executive at the Indonesian indigenous businessmen association (HIPPI), also expressed concern about the impact of the fuel price increase on the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the business sector. \par \par \uc2  "It is regrettable. Despite the already weak purchasing power of the people, they're still burdened with financing the (state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  "The fuel price increase will create an intense negative impact on the development of a people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he added. \par \par \uc2  The government, however, is confident that the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  can cope with increase. \par \par \uc2  "The President expects that the people can cope with this. It (the impact) has been thoroughly studied by a (government) team," Adhie Massardi, spokesman of President Abdurrahman Wahid, told reporters on Saturday. \par \par \uc2  The government initially planned to raise the fuel price on Friday, however the move was delayed pending a final social and political assessment, particularly amid massive labor protests in major cities across the country. \par \par \uc2  Several economists warned the government to delay the fuel price increase, saying time was needed to publicize the new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to avoid unrest. \par \par \uc2  Raising fuel prices has always been a politically sensitive issue in Indonesia. The downfall of former president Soeharto in 1998 was partly attributed to the fuel price increase in April that year. \par \par \uc2  Umar said that the fuel price increase would raise the inflation rate this year by 1.5 to 2 percentage points higher than the government's original projection of 9.3 percent. \par \par \uc2  He added that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity would also slow down due to the multiplier effect of the fuel price increase. \par \par \uc2  Umar said that the fuel price increase could trigger social unrest if the government failed to provide sufficient compensation to the people, particularly the poor. \par \par \uc2  The government has allocated around Rp 2.2 trillion in compensation for poor people badly affected by the fuel price increase. \par \par \uc2  The government will also provide compensation to operators of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  transportation such as city buses so that the cost of fares does not increase. \par \par \uc2  Umar also said that the government must cooperate with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  to deal with grievances from the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The government can't face the protest alone," he said. \par \par \uc2  The House has given its approval to the government fuel price increase \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Considering the current tension between President Abdurrahman Wahid and the House, however, it is difficult to imagine legislators defending the government against protesters of the fuel price increase \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The legislators had earlier asked the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), the country's supreme legislature, to hold a special session to call for the President's accountability. \par \par \uc2  IMF \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the International Monetary Fund (IMF), which is providing a multibillion dollar bailout program to the country, cautiously praised the decision. \par \par \uc2  "We support the government's move on fuel prices but the compensation package for the poor is a very important element of it and we still have to study that," IMF senior representative in Jakarta John Dodsworth told Reuters. \par \par \uc2  "For long term sustainability, the issue of fuel prices has to be dealt with, but the timing is very delicate. Only the government can make that decision. We cannot make that decision," Dodsworth added. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx6i001b6\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
