\par\par \b \uc2  Legislators regret RI's blacklisting. \b0\par\par\uc2 673 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 June 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Legislators expressed regret over the decision by industrialized nations to add Indonesia to a money laundering blacklist, saying it was not a wise step while the country was struggling to defuse a prolonged \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  Kwik Kian Gie, a legislator from the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan), said at present it was impossible for Indonesia to crack down on money laundering, since a majority of the laundered money deposited in banks was gained from corruption rather than other illegal activities such as the narcotics trade or smuggling. \par \par \uc2  "The majority of the bank deposits raised from corruption will move to other countries such as Singapore and Switzerland if the legal authorities are forced to investigate money laundering in the country," he told The Jakarta Post by telephone here on Saturday. \par \par \uc2  The Paris-based Financial Action Task Force, supported by industrialized nations, added Indonesia to a money laundering blacklist on Friday, threatening to recommend retaliatory actions against the country in international financial transactions. \par \par \uc2  Kwik, who is a former coordinating minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , said the government was unable to fight money laundering effectively because of a 1967 government \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  that bars law enforcers from monitoring bank deposits. \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  was issued by former president Soeharto when the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was at a low point and the inflation rate was 600 percent," he said, adding that the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  had yet to be revoked. \par \par \uc2  He said the government should revoke the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  and speed up the deliberation of a money laundering bill submitted early last week to allow for a gradual elimination of money laundering in the country's banking system. \par \par \uc2  According to the noted economist, if the government cracks down too hastily and too strenuously on money laundering it runs the risk of overseas capital flight. \par \par \uc2  "Indonesia needs capital and foreign investment for its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said that despite the absence of money laundering \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Indonesia could enforce the Criminal Code and other laws on banking, corruption and drugs to fight domestic and international syndicates involved in illegal activities. \par \par \uc2  Aberson Marle Sihaloho, another legislator from PDI Perjuangan, said the worldwide fight against money laundering should be coordinated by the UN to ensure equal treatment for all member countries. \par \par \uc2  He said industrialized countries should not only press crisis-hit countries such as Indonesia and Russia to eliminate money laundering, but all UN member countries, including Singapore and Switzerland, two countries that have been accused of storing the assets of corrupt regimes. \par \par \uc2  Aberson, a member of \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Commission IX for finance, banking and the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , warned the lion's share of Rp 850 trillion in bank deposits would move to Singapore as that country did not impose high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  on expatriates' assets. \par \par \uc2  "Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could collapse if the majority of the bank deposits owned by third parties were converted into US dollar and moved out," he said, adding that third parties preferred to deposit their capital in banks because of the political instability and legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country. \par \par \uc2  He said it would be futile for the government to issue a government \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  in lieu of law to crack down on money laundering because such a step would effect the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He said the industrialized nations' threat of retaliatory action against Indonesia would prove ineffective because international financial institutions, including the International Monetary Fund and the World Bank, were still disbursing loans to the country. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Ferry Mursyidan Baldan, deputy chairman of House Commission II for home and legal affairs, said it was impossible for the House to endorse the bill on money laundering this year because the House had many other bills that needed to be passed immediately. \par \par \uc2  "We have made it our priority to process bills that need to be passed into law to support the national system," he said, adding that the House has given the priority to bills on the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the settlement of labor disputes and the fight against corruption. (rms) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx6p005qq\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
