\par\par \b \uc2  BI sees 4.5% to 5.5% growth in 2002. \b0\par\par\uc2 588 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 June 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  predicted that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would enjoy higher growth of between 4.5 percent and 5.5 percent in 2002, compared to between 3 percent and 4 percent estimated for this year. \par \par \uc2  Speaking at a hearing session with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Commission IX on state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and finance on Tuesday, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin said that inflation next year would decline to a range of between 7 percent and 9 percent from between 8 percent and 10 percent in 2001. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said that the exchange rate of the rupiah could strengthen to between Rp 8,000 and Rp 9,000 per U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  He added, however, that this macroeconomic target could be achieved only if social and political problems were resolved and that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  restructuring program could be accelerated. \par \par \uc2  He particularly cautioned the slow progress in the restructuring of corporate overseas and domestic debts and in the restoration of the banking intermediation role that was still creating "serious" \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said that an improvement in the world's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  next year would have a positive effect on the local \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He said that domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in 2002 would be driven by exports, consumption and investment. \par \par \uc2  He said that a stronger exchange rate of the rupiah next year would help pull down inflation. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Sjahril said that the macroeconomic condition had not improved as significantly as expected at the beginning of this year due to the increase in risk and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He explained that the slow progress in the corporate restructuring program, deterioration in relations with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and the worsening domestic political conditions had caused confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to continue to plunge. \par \par \uc2  He added that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown in the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had also badly affected the local \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The worsening macroeconomic condition had prompted the government to revise the 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and adopt painful measures, including raising fuel prices by an average of 30 percent, and electricity rates by 17.47 percent to prevent the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  from widening to a dangerous level of 6 percent of gross domestic product (GDP). \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  now assumes an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 3.5 percent, inflation of 9.3 percent, and an exchange rate of 9,600 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  Separately, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Achjar Iljas said that the government might fail to achieve its 9.3 percent inflation target if the rupiah continued to weaken. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah is currently hovering at Rp 11,365 per dollar as investors continue to be jittery about the outcome of the People's Consultative Assembly's (MPR) plan to impeach President Abdurrahman Wahid on Aug. 1. \par \par \uc2  "It will be difficult to achieve the target, given the unfavorable circumstances," he said. \par \par \uc2  Economists predicted earlier that inflation this year could hit double digits of around 14 percent as the rupiah remained under pressure. \par \par \uc2  The lower value of the rupiah against the dollar increases production costs because the country's production system largely depends on imported raw materials and components. \par \par \uc2  But earlier on Monday, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Burhanuddin Abdullah expressed optimism that the government could achieve its 9.3 percent inflation target, citing improvements in the domestic political climate and better relations with the IMF, which is providing a multibillion dollar bailout for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Burhanuddin said that inflation in the first semester was normally high, but would decline in the second semester.(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx6r005x8\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
