\par\par \b \uc2  Economists warn govt over 2001  \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 619 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 June 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Economists warned that the government might fail to maintain the 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at a safe level of 3.7 percent of gross domestic product (GDP) due to problems in collecting higher \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue. \par \par \uc2  Dradjat H. Wibowo of the Institute for Development of Economics and Finance (Indef) said on Thursday with the remaining six-month period in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  it would be impossible to collect some Rp 185.26 trillion in \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue. \par \par \uc2  "There will not be enough time to step up \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collections, not enough time to widen \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  coverage and not enough time to increase \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  ratio," he said, adding that amid the current domestic political turbulence \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection would be even more difficult to implement. \par \par \uc2  "The government may effectively have only four months to collect \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  Dradjat said the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  would widen to 4.49 percent, or border on the psychologically dangerous 5 percent of GDP. \par \par \uc2  He was speaking at a seminar on Indef's mid-year assessment of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and business climate \par \par \uc2  Experts including the International Monetary Fund (IMF) have earlier warned that the 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  could widen to 6 percent of GDP due to the sharp drop in the value of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar, and rising domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The government earlier this month raised fuel prices by an average of 30 percent and electricity rates are to rise by 20 percent in a bid to contain the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 3.7 percent of GDP. But the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  rejected the government proposal to raise value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (VAT) to 12.5 percent from the current 10 percent. \par \par \uc2  Dradjat further said that if the government failed to obtain a debt rescheduling facility from the Paris Club of creditor nations, the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  could balloon to more than 6.5 percent of GDP. \par \par \uc2  There has been concern that the Paris Club might decline to reschedule some US$2.7 billion in the country's sovereign debt maturing this year due to worsening relations with the IMF. \par \par \uc2  The Paris Club had indicated that it would only implement the debt rescheduling if the government managed to secure a new deal with the IMF, a matter which remains \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  due to a dispute over the controversial amendment of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law. \par \par \uc2  However, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Burhanuddin Abdullah said on Wednesday that he expected the IMF's review team to arrive in Jakarta next month. \par \par \uc2  He said that the government was now willing to compromise over the contentious \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law issue. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile Indef's director Bustanul Arifin said that the institute expected the rupiah be hovering in the range of Rp 9,000-Rp 10,000 per U.S. dollar this year. \par \par \uc2  The government has targeted the average exchange rate of the rupiah for this year at Rp 9,600 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  Bustanul said overall he expected an improved trend in exchange rates at the end of this year, but that daily rates are expected to fluctuate sharply especially leading toward the House's special session. \par \par \uc2  The People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), the country's highest \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body, is scheduled to hold a special session on Aug. 1, possibly resulting in the impeachment of President Abdurrahman Wahid. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been under strong pressure particularly amid domestic political instability as Abdurrahman has been facing political pressure to step down. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended at Rp 11,440 per dollar late on Thursday, down from Rp 11,395. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Bustanul predicted that the rupiah could improve to Rp 8,500 per dollar over the next two to three years. (tnt) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010912dx6t0003t\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
