\par\par \b \uc2  BI signals higher local rates despite Fed rate cut. \b0\par\par\uc2 522 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 June 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said on Friday that lowering local rates to adjust them in line with the United States' Federal Reserve Bank (Fed)'s interest rate cut was untimely, and warned that domestic rates might even rise further. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin said cutting local rates would not be appropriate given Indonesia's current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions. \par \par \uc2  "The time isn't right for us to lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but whether they will continue to rise, we'll have to see," he told reporters after a closed-door meeting with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  commission. \par \par \uc2  The Fed on Wednesday cut its federal funds rate - the rate used for overnight interbank loans - by a slight 25 basis points to 3.75 percent. \par \par \uc2  The Fed's latest interest rate cut marked the sixth reduction in its federal funds rate since early this year to help cope with a slowdown in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Before the rate stood at 6.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  A reduction in the Fed's rates often triggers central banks in other countries to follow suit, particularly those whose currencies are pegged to the U.S dollar. \par \par \uc2  But in contrast, Indonesia's SBI rates have been steadily rising this year. \par \par \uc2  From around 14 percent early this year, the SBI (benchmark) rate rose to 16.65 percent at the latest auction on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said earlier the tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was necessary as Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was different. \par \par \uc2  While other countries slash \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to spur \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, Indonesia has been increasing its rates to reduce pressure on the rupiah and, consequently, reduce inflationary pressures. \par \par \uc2  But analysts are in doubt whether higher \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  are still effective in controlling inflation and the rupiah rates. \par \par \uc2  Since March, the year-on-year inflation rate has been hovering at over 10 percent. The government's target is 9.3 percent. \par \par \uc2  Upward pressure on inflation is likely to increase, given the government's move to hike fuel and electricity prices and the weakening rupiah which raises the cost of imports. \par \par \uc2  On the foreign exchange market, the rupiah is still performing below the government's assumption of 9,800 against the U.S dollar for the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah closed at 11,410 to the dollar on Friday afternoon. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's reliance on SBI rates to meet its monetary targets is also contributing to a widening state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  A large portion of bank recapitalization bonds, worth Rp 430 trillion (about US$38 billion), carry \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  tied to the SBI rate. \par \par \uc2  The higher the SBI rate, the more interest the government must pay on the bonds. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Deputy Governor Miranda Goeltom said that \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  are likely to increase, citing lingering \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Instability and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  are causing money to flow into the market. We're trying to get that money and prevent it from being used for speculation," she explained. \par \par \uc2  Miranda was referring to the ongoing political dispute between President Abdurrahman Wahid and legislators, which has become a catalyst for speculative trading in the money market. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010912dx6u0006n\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
