\par\par \b \uc2  Business confidence continues to worsen - Survey. \b0\par\par\uc2 545 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 July 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Business confidence again fell in the April-May period due to domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , according to a survey conducted by the Danareksa Research Institute. \par \par \uc2  Danareksa said in a report released on Monday that the business sentiment index fell to 110.1 from 113.8 on losses in both the present situation index and the expectations index. \par \par \uc2  The agency said the drop in the two indexes was due to the "sharp erosion of investor confidence in the government". \par \par \uc2  The survey involved some 700 CEOs and directors of companies from various sectors. \par \par \uc2  The current domestic leadership crisis and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  woes have created jitters among businesspeople. The People's Consultative Assembly, the country's top \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body, is planning to hold a special session on Aug. 1 that could lead to the impeachment of the embattled President Abdurrahman Wahid. \par \par \uc2  According to the survey, sentiment about the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition fell 8.24 percent in view of the deteriorating business environment on the back of growing political tensions. \par \par \uc2  The index that measures business conditions declined by 3 percent, as businesspeople felt the brunt of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political instability, with all key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  variables straying farther from their business assumptions, the agency said. \par \par \uc2  As such, the businesspeople expected prices and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to go further north and the exchange rate and the composite price index to go further south, broadly dampening corporate prospects, the agency said. \par \par \uc2  According to the survey, the confidence of businesspeople in their own companies slipped slightly to 148.8 from 149.9 on the back of across-the-board declines in the sentiment on capital \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , sales, profit, liquidity and the use of production capacity and labor. \par \par \uc2  The agency said the increasingly grim \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook pulled sentiment down by 7 percent to 72.7 from 78.1, as the short-term effects of the current political turmoil could be hugely destabilizing in fragile political situations. \par \par \uc2  The sentiment on the business outlook also weakened 4.3 percent in the face of a crumbling rupiah and rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  that have pushed up the cost of debt servicing, the agency said. \par \par \uc2  "With a bleak picture of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , confidence in the corporate outlook also lowered to 153.9 from 156.2, as business executives are wary of companies' growth prospects," the agency said. \par \par \uc2  The agency said the prospects for an imminent recovery for both the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and companies looked slim, with the rupiah more likely to weaken than strengthen. \par \par \uc2  Businesspeople will take a bigger hit from all angles given the rising spiral of inflation-depreciation that would be further ignited by likely rises in SBI (\b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory notes) rates, fuel and electricity prices, the agency said. \par \par \uc2  "They are squeezed between lower sales revenues and higher costs, with profits on the wane," the agency said, adding that it was too risky to proceed with any business plans, even if the unpredictable risks could be reliably hedged, with the risk premium difficult to assess in advance. \par \par \uc2  Accordingly, there will only be a sparse appetite for new business deals, since a decrease in labor hiring and capital \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the next six months, coupled with higher jobless rates, appear on the cards, the agency concluded. (03) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010710dx7a0005y\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
