\par\par \b \uc2  IMF to disburse loan by the end of August - Akbar. \b0\par\par\uc2 509 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 July 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The International Monetary Fund (IMF) said it expected to disburse its stalled US$400 million loan tranche to Indonesia by the end of August, \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Speaker Akbar Tandjung claimed on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  "Mr. Anoop Singh said the disbursement would be effected sometime late in August," Akbar said referring to the visiting IMF Asia Pacific deputy director, who made a courtesy call on the House speaker. \par \par \uc2  Most analysts have predicted that the IMF would not make any decision until after the special session of the People's Consultative Assembly beginning on Aug.1. \par \par \uc2  The Assembly is widely expected to withdraw President Abdurrahman Wahid's mandate, and a new government is predicted to emerge sometime in mid-August. \par \par \uc2  Akbar said the IMF made no reference to the special session. \par \par \uc2  "But they did ask me about the political situation, which I clarified to them briefly," he said. \par \par \uc2  Akbar added that he explained to the IMF about the Assembly's special session and how it could help restore political stability. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have said that the IMF is likely to defer the loan disbursement until some of the current political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  have been cleared up. \par \par \uc2  Should a new president be elected, questions will surface over the lineup of the next cabinet and the ministers to be placed in charge of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Burhanuddin Abdullah said earlier that he expected a new letter of intent (LoI) to be signed within the week, citing Friday or Saturday as the possible day of signing. \par \par \uc2  The LoI will contain a set of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform targets Indonesia must meet to ensure the continuation of the IMF's financial aid. \par \par \uc2  Following the signing of the LoI, the IMF team will head back to Washington to submit the document to the IMF executive board for approval, a process that usually takes about two to three weeks. \par \par \uc2  But IMF First Deputy Managing Director Stanley Fischer said in Tokyo that political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  instability made it too early to say whether a loan disbursement was possible next month. \par \par \uc2  "What Burhanuddin says is entirely possible ... not certain by any means because of the potential instability," Fischer was quoted as saying by Dow Jones. \par \par \uc2  According to him, slow bank and corporate sector restructuring remained a major concern. \par \par \uc2  Akbar went on to say that the IMF did not specifically mention when they expected a new LoI to be signed. \par \par \uc2  "But it is most likely that they (the IMF) will complete their work later this week," he claimed. \par \par \uc2  He said the IMF told him that the latest LoI would cover no new items and was essentially identical to the current one which was signed in September. \par \par \uc2  "They are discussing the old LoI again, and it appears that there won't be many differences in terms of substance," he said. \par \par \uc2  Akbar added that the IMF had confirmed to him that the new LoI contained fewer reform targets, as hinted at earlier by government officials.(bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx7c0006f\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
