\par\par \b \uc2  IMF tells govt to keep on track with next LoI. \b0\par\par\uc2 684 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 July 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The International Monetary Fund (IMF) reminded the government on Thursday to abide by the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform targets to be set in the next letter of intent (LoI) and urged it to show strong discipline in meeting the targets. \par \par \uc2  "The important thing is for the government to implement the program on track, (be) systematic, consistent and predictable. That's what the market is waiting for," IMF Asia Pacific deputy director Anoop Singh told reporters after he made a courtesy call on Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri. \par \par \uc2  Singh's statement came as a reminder of the government's poor record in meeting reform targets under the current LoI. \par \par \uc2  The slow pace and inconsistency that have marred the implementation of the LoI prompted the IMF to suspend its loan program in December. \par \par \uc2  Meeting the LoI targets, which are aimed at leading the country out of its almost four-year-long \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, is mandatory for receiving IMF funds. \par \par \uc2  But Indonesian government economists blamed the political instability for the slowdown in the reform program. \par \par \uc2  "We understand (Indonesia's situation) ... in the long term, you will see the market understands that as well," Singh said. \par \par \uc2  To date, the market demands Indonesia show consistency in implementing the LoI, he added. \par \par \uc2  The suspension of the IMF loan has also hurt the rupiah, as other international creditors and investors link their commitments to the IMF's ties with Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  With a new LoI in sight, the government now hopes the IMF may soon disburse its frozen US$400 million loan tranche. \par \par \uc2  According to Singh, negotiation between the IMF and the government is edging toward an end. \par \par \uc2  "We're finalizing our understanding on all fields, and we need just a bit more time," he said. \par \par \uc2  Singh said that discussion with the government was based on the progress made under the current LoI, from where they would draw up a new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program. \par \par \uc2  "We're looking at the weaknesses of the old LoI to prepare the new LoI," he explained. \par \par \uc2  The next LoI, he said, will cover targets in the monetary sector, the banking sector, the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the programs under the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA). \par \par \uc2  "The government is now reviewing its targets and may announce them tomorrow (Friday)," he explained. \par \par \uc2  Singh, however, declined to estimate when he expected the IMF to disburse the tranche. \par \par \uc2  Economics ministers have aired their confidence that Indonesia could expect fresh funds in August. \par \par \uc2  But \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the country's leadership have subdued hopes of disbursement in the first two weeks of next month. \par \par \uc2  The People's Consultative Assembly, the country's top legislature, is scheduled to convene a special session on Aug. 1, which could lead to the removal of Abdurrahman Wahid as president. \par \par \uc2  During his meeting with Megawati, Singh also said that he reiterated the IMF's continued commitment to Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "We (IMF) need to be patient, because it does take time for Indonesia, as other countries also do, to recover from the crisis," he said. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would raise its intervention rate to absorb excess money supply in the market. \par \par \uc2  "What remains to be done is to raise the intervention rate," he announced after a meeting with the IMF team. \par \par \uc2  He said the move would help reduce the supply of base money to between Rp 105 trillion (about $9.29 billion) to Rp 106 trillion from the current Rp 112 trillion. \par \par \uc2  The overnight intervention rate is currently at 14.125 percent. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has relied mostly on its interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to help the ailing rupiah and has steadily raised its benchmark rate to as high as the current 16.91 percent. \par \par \uc2  But the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has little room left to continue this \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as a further rise would hurt the banking sector and inflict a bigger burden on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for servicing the bank recapitalization bonds. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril added that the bank would lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  once the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which has fueled rupiah speculation, eased. (bkm/dja) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010713dx7d00065\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
