\par\par \b \uc2  2001 INFLATION RATE TO END UP HIGHER THAN PROJECTED. \b0\par\par\uc2 338 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 July 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited.< Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its\par \par \uc2  Jakarta, July 20 (ANTARA) - \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) indicated here Friday the country's inflation rate for 2001 is expected to range between nine and 11 percent, up from a previous projection of six to 8.5 percent. In a statement issued at the end of BI Board of Governors' meeting, the bank said political as well as \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  were the main factors in the rate's upward movement during the second quarter of 2001. It said the 9-11 percent projection was realistic, considering the pressure of ongoing commodity price hikes and the need to maintain monetary stability. But whether the projection would come true would also depend on the effectivenese of efforts to bring about \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms, restore \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  confidence and eliminate \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . During the second quarter of 2001, the rupiah depreciated continuously and moved with high volatility, the bank said. \par \par \uc2   The national currency dropped to Rp11,230 against the US dollar or by 13.4 percent from its position in the first quarter of 2001, the bank reported. Inflation during the second quarter of 2001 had reached 3.28 percent, compared to 2.11 percent in the first quarter of the year. During the second quarter of 2000, the inflation rate stood at 12.11 percent. The cumulative inflation rate at the end of the second quarter of 2001 reached 5.46 percent, the BI said. \par \par \uc2  Banking industry Referring to developments in the banking industry, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said up to the end of the second quarter of 2001 no signficant progress had been made in terms of the industry's health. Slight progress was recorded in some areas, for instance an increase in banks' lending rate from 2.4 percent to 2.8 percent, accumulation of third party funds, a positive net interest margin, and a lower ratio in non performing loans (NPL). The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said it would maintain its tight money \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in a bid to control the inflation rate. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010725dx7k00060\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
