\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia \highlight\uc2  sees inflation up at 9%-11%. \b0\par\par\uc2 740 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 July 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  expects inflation this year to be between 9 percent and 11 percent, higher than the initial target range of between 6 percent to 8.5 percent, and predicts a weaker \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the second semester due to persistent \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and risk factors. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said on Friday that the continued weakening of the rupiah, coupled with government pricing policies, including on fuel, had driven prices upwards. \par \par \uc2  Since March, the year on year inflation rates have reached 10 percent, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  sees an inflation rate forecast of between 9 percent and 11 percent as a realistic scenario," the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said in its second quarter \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  report. \par \par \uc2  But it added the target range depended on the government's ability to improve the supply and distribution chain of products and on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms. \par \par \uc2  Proper implementation of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms will help regain business confidence and reduce \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and risk factors, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, it said, is likely to be in the neighborhood of 3.5 percent this year, less than the previous target of between 4.5 percent and 5.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  The bank said the revised \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth rate rested on expectations that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  weaknesses in the previous two quarters were likely to extend through the rest of the year. \par \par \uc2  It said the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had slowed down in the second quarter, as it grew by only between 3 percent and 4 percent compared to 4.1 percent during the first quarter. \par \par \uc2  "In the second quarter, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was still able to grow albeit at a slow pace," the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  blamed the slow down on the country's heated political situation, slow corporate and foreign debt restructuring, the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the relations between the government and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and on the still crippled intermediary role of the banking sector. \par \par \uc2  These factors have raised the cost of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  transactions, thus slowing down investments. \par \par \uc2  It said that risk factors, caused by political and other \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , posed a greater harm to investment activities than the impact of higher lending rates by banks. \par \par \uc2  Throughout the second quarter investment grew by only 7.5 percent compared to 10.2 percent in the first quarter, it said. \par \par \uc2  On the demand side, the bank estimated consumption and export growth to remain the driving force of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  However, export growth had weakened to 8 percent in the second quarter, as against 11.7 percent in the first. \par \par \uc2  On the supply side, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  cited declines in the manufacturing, trading, service and mining sectors. \par \par \uc2  But growth in the agriculture and construction sectors fared better in the second quarter than the first one. \par \par \uc2  For the entire year, export would remain sluggish partly as several Indonesian export markets were hit by an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown. \par \par \uc2  "Although export could still rise on a weaker rupiah, slackened domestic investment and production \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  have reduced foreign demand (for Indonesian products), which in turn hampers exports," the bank said. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  further estimated that pressure on the rupiah is likely to continue throughout the third quarter. \par \par \uc2  "This is because of continued political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the persistently thin foreign currency market," the bank said. \par \par \uc2  However, it expected improvements on the political front to bring the rupiah's average rate for this year to a range of Rp 9,800 to Rp 10,600 against the U.S dollar. \par \par \uc2  The stage \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumes an average rupiah rate of Rp 9,600 to the dollar. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said the plunge in the rupiah value came on the back of speculation and poorer market expectation on the local unit. \par \par \uc2  It said the rupiah's prolonged depreciation had created a spiraling effect, increasing financial risks and consequently the cost of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  transactions. \par \par \uc2  Commenting on the banking sector, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said it would provide banks with an exit \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  if they failed to meet the minimum capital adequacy ratio (CAR) of 8 percent by Dec. 31. \par \par 