\par\par \b \uc2  Gains from perceived stability. \b0\par\par\uc2 617 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 July 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The almost 14 percent appreciation of the rupiah against the U.S.dollar immediately after the dismissal of Abdurrahman Wahid from the presidency last week shows how enormous have been the damages on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  inflicted by his erratic leadership. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah and the stock market have been strengthening since early last week entirely because the end of Abdurrahman's presidency was seen as a resolution to the political impasse and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and an end to the confusion and chaos in the decision and \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -making machinery. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah appreciation is simply due to the market perception that the overall outlook now will most likely be a stable environment, a predictable \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -making process and a cooperative legislature, which are prerequisites for pushing ahead with the reform agenda. \par \par \uc2  One may argue that so far the improvements have only been in the financial market, which is highly vulnerable to rumors and speculative transactions, and that they are not related to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals or the real sector. Yet the positive indicators cannot be simply discounted as a market game of speculators. \par \par \uc2  In fact, the steady weakening of the rupiah, especially over the past 12 months when former president Abdurrahman was preoccupied with defending his power with all sorts of tactics at the expense of national stability, has been one of the primary causes of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  bleeding. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah depreciation alone has caused a chain of damages on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , forcing a mid-term revision of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and making debt restructuring more difficult. The rising costs of imports have forced the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to maintain a tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to curb inflationary pressures. This credit crunch in turn has hurt business operations, threatening the weak banking industry with further capital erosion and the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  with an unsustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The positive market signal will surely be a valuable asset for the new president, Megawati Soekarnoputri, to embark on her immense task of addressing the array of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and social problems. \par \par \uc2  This does not, however, mean the tasks facing the Megawati administration will be less challenging. In fact, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  bleeding over the past year has made the problems more daunting. \par \par \uc2  The most pressing and urgent agenda remain centered on corporate debt and bank restructuring, recovery of the huge pool of assets currently managed by the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) and privatization of state companies. All these, like the weakening rupiah, have been responsible for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  bleeding. Consequently, this bleeding has to be stopped to maintain the budding \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  No wonder, analysts are waiting eagerly for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team of the new Cabinet to be announced this week as Megawati's performance will be judged primarily on her administration's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance. \par \par \uc2  Whether the market gains from the fall of Abdurrahman's administration will strengthen or weaken, will depend on the caliber of the those appointed to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  portfolios. \par \par \uc2  If the new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team consists of well-respected professionals of high integrity whom the business community is comfortable with, the market perception of the new administration will become more positive even before the new Cabinet starts to prove its worth. On the other hand, the new Cabinet can plunge into an inimical market environment if the integrity and competence of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team are sacrificed for political interests in the formation of a coalition Cabinet. \par \par \uc2  Unfortunately, President Megawati will not have the privilege of a honeymoon period as most new administrations do. She should soon come up with a credible \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team and a cohesive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to convince the market, the International Monetary Fund and creditors of the Consultative Group for Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010731dx7v0005v\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
