r \par \uc2  MINISTERS SHOULD BE CLEAN The meeting between President Megawati Soekarnoputri and Vice President Hamzah Haz yesterday (Monday) seemed to have eased the setting up of the new cabinet's format and the choice of ministers. It seems unavoidable for the new cabinet to have more ministers than that of the administration of former president, Abdurrahman Wahid. Amid all the problems faced by the nation, the people have high expectations of the new cabinet. They expect the coordinating ministers and ministers to make the right programs to lead the nation out of its crisis. The ministers are also expected to be highly credible whom the people could trust. Regarding this, it would be normal if the ministers declare their wealth and obligations as ordinary citizens, for instance for \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  purposes. By fulfilling these expectations, the ministers will be good role models for the society. - Bisnis Indonesia \par \par \uc2  JAIL MANAGEMENT Prison is a sub-system which reflects the bigger system. A lousy prison is the result of a lousy system. The escape of Edi Tanzil has yet to be solved. That is not the only case of jailbreak in Indonesia. In February, two prisoners, one of whom was Ibrahim AMD Abdul Wahab - a suspect in the bombing of the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) - broke out of the Cipinang Penitentiary. A month later in March, a number of prisoners also broke out of prison after starting a fire in Cipinang and taking a prisoner hostage. Was that the end? No. Last Friday, a prisoner again escaped from Cipinang. He was Irwan bin Ilyas, another suspect in the JSX bombing. Irwan's escape compelled the East Jakarta district police to make a sweep of Cipinang. In the sweep, they found a lot of guns and illegal drugs. No wonder it was easy for Tanzil and the other prisoners to break out of prison. The management of this jail is extremely soft and fragile, making jailbreaks easy. The key to this mess is the badness of those in charge of prison. They are ready to give comfort in exchange for bribes. The new government brings new hope. This government will not last long, only three years. Not many problems are expected to be solved during this short time. Anyhow, it would be good enough if the government could stabilize the rupiah, put corruptors in jail, and prevent them from escaping. - Media Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010803dx7v0005o\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
