\par\par \b \uc2  Indonesia seeks to improve debt rating. \b0\par\par\uc2 710 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 August 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The new economics team aims to improve the country's credit rating from the current non-investment rating to investment grade within six months, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti said on Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun said that the debt rating upgrade would allow both the country and its business sectors to tap international funds at an affordable cost. \par \par \uc2  "We will immediately seek to improve our image before the international community," Dorodjatun told reporters at a press meeting following the first \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers' meeting of the new government. \par \par \uc2  "If we achieve that, we can return to the international money market," he said. \par \par \uc2  International rating agencies had cut the country's debt rating to non-investment grade due to domestic political problems and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  woes. \par \par \uc2  Standard & Poor's has assigned a CCC+ on Indonesia's long term foreign currency rating, according to Dorodjatun. \par \par \uc2  He said with a CCC+ rating, Indonesia has been classified as a non-investment country by the rating agency. \par \par \uc2  He expected Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political conditions to continue to progress sufficiently well within the next five to six months for a rating of BB. \par \par \uc2  Last week Dorodjatun said Indonesia's low credit rating made it difficult to seek affordable funds from the money market. \par \par \uc2  "Our rating isn't good, the additional interest spread that shows Indonesia's risk, is still high," he said. \par \par \uc2  "They (Standard & Poor's) won't disclose the interest spread, but my guess is that it's well above the American government bonds, which is a world benchmark," he added. \par \par \uc2  He said the spread could be as high as 600 to 700 basis points, where 100 points reflects 1 percent. \par \par \uc2  "For developing countries the usual spread should be around 300 to 400 basis points, or 3 to 4 percentage points above the 10-year U.S. bonds," he explained. \par \par \uc2  By Standard & Poor's definition, an insurer rated CCC is currently vulnerable and is dependent upon favorable business, financial and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions to meet its financial commitments. \par \par \uc2  At BB, the insurer is less vulnerable, but faces major ongoing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and exposures to adverse business, financial or \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions. \par \par \uc2  These could lead to the insurer's incapacity to meet its financial commitments. \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun said that at BB, Indonesia's importers would find it easier to open a Letter of Credit (L/C) with foreign banks. \par \par \uc2  "With BB, importers don't have to go to Singapore or Hong Kong to open L/Cs," he said. \par \par \uc2  An L/C is a payment guarantee issued by a bank to temporarily cover the payments of its customer to a foreign bank. \par \par \uc2  Since the 1997 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis struck the country, many local banks' L/Cs have been rejected by their foreign counterparts. \par \par \uc2  But the real benefit of an improved credit rating was the cheaper foreign funds required to invest in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  Economist Faisal Basri said the government would lend the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  a major boost if it could improve Indonesia's rating. \par \par \uc2  "If the credit rating improves, foreign investment will return, debt burden will ease, companies will get back on track to reschedule their debts," he said. \par \par \uc2  Faisal said the government could achieve a BB rating within six months time providing it does all its "homework." \par \par \uc2  The preparation, he said, was taking the necessary measures to meet the 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  target of 3.7 percent of gross domestic product and drafting the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  prior to the meeting of the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI). \par \par \uc2  CGI groups together Indonesian donor countries to help it finance its development \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun said earlier Indonesia must present to the CGI a clean and convincing state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as a prerequisite for receiving the group's aid. \par \par \uc2  The CGI meeting is slated for October and Dorodjatun said he hoped the meeting would be held in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Securing a lending agreement with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) was another target the government must meet, Faisal continued. \par \par \uc2  Credit rating agencies have cut Indonesia's rating partly on the IMF's suspension of its loan program to the country late last year after the previous government failed to implement a number of major \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs.(bkm/03/tnt) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010815dx8f00063\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
