\par\par \b \uc2  TUESDAY Aug 28 2001 EDITORIALS IN MAJOR INDONESIAN DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 649 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 August 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  NEW INTENT TO REFORM The fewer programs of action stipulated in the new Letter of Intent (LoI) signed by the Indonesian government and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) on Monday do not indicate a fewer daunting reforms ahead. Nor does it reflect a more relaxed stance on the part of the IMF with regard to the disbursement of its extended facility. The challenges ahead are even more formidable as the government has to speed up reform measures to redress the damages caused by delay of the many painful programs under previous administration of Abdurrahman Wahid. The US$400 million, which will be disbursed by the IMF in the third tranche of its US$5 billion fund within the next few weeks, cannot be used for the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  as it is designed only as a second line of defense within the country's foreign reserve. Without additional debt-rescheduling packages from the Paris Club, the government's capital account will suffer an increasingly bigger amount of net resource outflow. \par \par \uc2   Set against this severe liquidity crisis, private investment should be the prime source of fuel to drive the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The problem, though, is that private investors will remain on the sidelines, unless macroeconomic stability is restored and the degree of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the business climate is minimized. It is therefore no exaggeration to say that a successful execution of this reform agreement could be the last chance for the government to revive investor confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . More backtracking would make Indonesia a basket case in the eyes of both creditors and investors. - The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2  BITTERNESS WITH IMF The LOI and the IMF. These are the most awesome words for Indonesia's leaders. The LOI - Letter of Intent - is not merely a line of requirements but a deadly sword, and the IMF, International Monetary Fund, could turn into a cruel godfather, a boss who knows well that a country in crisis, like Indonesia, could not do anything but to bow to all requirements set by lenders. In fact, the IMF loans have so many times been delayed because of some differences. This happened during Abdurrahman Wahid's administration. The LOI which has been delayed since December 2000, now has found its way toward the disbursement of the US$ 400 million loan. Only a month and four days after President Megawati Soekarnoputri took office, the LOI was signed. So easy. This has shown the IMF's subjectivity in the disbursement of its loans. If the organization wants to, anything can be easy. All problems that hampered the disbursement of the loan during Wahid's term has become insignificant. Yesterday's (Monday's) LOI explained two things. First, the IMF seems happy with the current government and second, the new government has built its credibility. However, we have to learn from our past experience that both the IMF and the Indonesian government should be fair and must build mutual trust. Indonesia has to be fair in implementing the agreement while the IMF should see Indonesia with all its weaknesses. Hopefully, this would be the last LOI which has to pass through a deadlock. The IMF and Indonesia have to learn from arrogance and unfairness to end their bitter experiences. - Media Indonesia \par \par \uc2  PARTY CADRES SHOULD BE COMPETENT Nowadays, it is not enough for a party cadre to have spirit alone. He or she must also be competent so that the party would not be sidelined in many fields in a more global and democratic life. We see that many cadres still have to do what they call comparative studies abroad or in some local universities at the expense of the people. This only attracts criticisms. We do know that preparing capable cadres need time, thus political parties must start focusing their attention on this issue. Otherwise, they will be abandoned by the people. - Republika. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010830dx8s00002\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  LoI is focused on six main programs. \b0\par\par\uc2 640 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 August 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The new Letter of Intent (LoI), signed by the \par \par \uc2  Indonesian \par \par \uc2  government yesterday, is focused on six crucial programs considered \par \par \uc2  important to revive the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The six programs include: Macroeconomic framework and policies; \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  decentralization; Banking reform; IBRA asset restructuring and \par \par \uc2  recovery; \par \par \uc2  Legal reform and corporate restructuring; and Reform in the government \par \par \uc2  sector and other structural reforms. \par \par \uc2  "The programs are crusial for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery process," head of \par \par \uc2  the \par \par \uc2  IMF mission Anoop Singh said during a press conference after the \par \par \uc2  signing of \par \par \uc2  the memorandum at the Finance Ministry yesterday. \par \par \uc2  The LoI which is signed by Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun \par \par \uc2  Kuntjori-Jakti, Finance Minister Boediono and BI Governor Syahril \par \par \uc2  Sabirin is \par \par \uc2  the third under the extended fund facility (EFF) approved in January \par \par \uc2  2000, \par \par \uc2  in the era of President Wahid. The US$4.68 billion worth EFF-often \par \par \uc2  round up \par \par \uc2  to US$5 billion-since it was approved has only been disbursed US$1.106 \par \par \uc2  billion. \par \par \uc2  Under the normal procedure, the IMF executive board would hold a \par \par \uc2  meeting two \par \par \uc2  weeks after the LoI signing to approve loan disbursement worth US$400 \par \par \uc2  million, said Singh. \par \par \uc2  "Based on a normal procedure, the executive board will meet to discuss \par \par \uc2  loan \par \par \uc2  disbursement," said Singh. \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun, on behalf of the government stated his gratitude for the \par \par \uc2  cooperation shown by the IMF mission throughout the week when \par \par \uc2  discussing the \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs (letter of intent) with the Indonesian government. \par \par \uc2  As for Anoop Singh, his mission in Jakarta would be his last as an IMF \par \par \uc2  official because he will be replaced by Daniel Citrin. \par \par \uc2  Balance of payment \par \par \uc2  Finance Minister Boediono said the amount of loan the IMF plans to \par \par \uc2  disburse \par \par \uc2  remains US$400 million despite the nine-month delay. The fund, he \par \par \uc2  added, is \par \par \uc2  not to finance \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  but will be used to support payment \par \par \uc2  balance \par \par \uc2  sheet, which will be included under foreign \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Boediono also hoped the fund can be disbursed within the next two \par \par \uc2  weeks. "As \par \par \uc2  already mentioned by Anoop Singh, the executive board meeting is two \par \par \uc2  weeks \par \par \uc2  after the LoI signing," he added. \par \par \uc2  According to Boediono, the LoI signing was crucial for reviving \par \par \uc2  overseas \par \par \uc2  investor confidence and for obtaining agreement from the Paris Club of \par \par \uc2  creditor nations to reschedule 2.8 billion dollars in debts. \par \par \uc2  The IMF has so far disbursed US$10.8 billion loan to Indonesia, while \par \par \uc2  its \par \par \uc2  liability position as per 31 July is US$10.097 billion, after the \par \par \uc2  government \par \par \uc2  paid US$715 million from December 2000 to 31 July. \par \par \uc2  The amount of liability due this year reaches US$1.3 billion, and \par \par \uc2  US$2.7 \par \par \uc2  billion next year. \par \par \uc2  In an interview with the Business Times in Singapore when accompanying \par \par \uc2  President Megawati, Dorodjatun said the discussion with the IMF \par \par \uc2  produced \par \par \uc2  three important points. First, is how the government would deal with \par \par \uc2  huge \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  years, secondly is the effort to \par \par \uc2  stabilize \par \par \uc2  the rupiah, and last is IBRA's efforts to accelerate asset sales. \par \par \uc2  He explained that the asset sales are continued although they are \par \par \uc2  unlikely \par \par \uc2  to meet the Rp37 trillion target, including cash and bonds. \par \par \uc2  Depending on the parliament \par \par \uc2  Separately, Chairman of the New Indonesia Association Syahrir said \par \par \uc2  yesterday \par \par \uc2  's LoI signing was a progress for Indonesia. But added, there are more \par \par \uc2  challenges ahead. \par \par \uc2  The key to the next solution lies in the hand of the parliament, said \par \par \uc2  Syahrir. He called on the parliament members to proactively takeover \par \par \uc2  issues \par \par \uc2  that required the Fund's approval immediately. \par \par \uc2  "At least before the IMF executive board commences its meeting in \par \par \uc2  Washington," he said in a seminar yesterday. \par \par \uc2  He reminded the parliament to put into priority problems that have to \par \par \uc2  be \par \par \uc2  solved in clear conscience. So, we don't want to see the \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  refusing to sign for \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  reasons. "It could be troublesome [for \par \par \uc2  the \par \par \uc2  implementation of the IMF programs]." (m04/01/ab). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010828dx8s00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
